Source: radish-bdd
Maintainer: Timo Furrer <tuxtimo@gmail.com>
Section: python
Priority: optional
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), dh-python,
 python-all (>= 2.7.3), python-setuptools,
 python3-all, python3-setuptools
Standards-Version: 3.9.1

Package: radish-bdd
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${python:Depends},
Description: Behavior Driven Development tool for python
 radish is a Behavior Driven Development tool completely written in python.
 It supports all gherkin language features. In addition to that,
 radish implements a few unconventional BDD features such as Preconditions,
 Scenario Loops, Constants and Expressions.

